
---

@startuml

class User {
  +id: String
  +name: String
  +email: String
  +dateOfBirth: Date
}

class Account {
  +accountNumber: String
  +type: String (Personal/Business)
  -user: User
}

class PersonalAccount extends Account {
  +isVerified: Boolean
}

class BusinessAccount extends Account {
  +companyName: String
  +monthlyFee: Double
}

class Page {
  +name: String
  +visitCount: Integer
  -account: Account
}

class AdvertisementPage extends Page {
  +bounceRate: Double
  +clickThroughRate: Double
  +conversionRate: Double
}

User "1" -- "1" Account : creates
Account "1" -- "0..*" Page : manages
PersonalAccount "1" -- "0..*" Page : can be granted privileges to
BusinessAccount "1" -- "1" AdvertisementPage : can create
Page "1" -- "1" Account : managed by

@enduml

---

### Explanation of Relationships:

- **User → Account**: A user can create one account.
- **Account → Page**: An account can manage multiple pages.
- **PersonalAccount → Page**: A personal account can be granted privileges to other personal account's pages.
- **BusinessAccount → AdvertisementPage**: A business account can create advertisement pages.
- **Page → Account**: Each page is managed by exactly one account.
- **User → PersonalAccount / BusinessAccount**: A user can have either a personal or business account, but not both.

